THE USAGE OF THE PROGRAM


collins.exe -UNPOL 0

will generate unpolarised cross-sections in all bins of SOLID for pi+ and pi-.
Stored in files 
solid_unpolarised_3he_pim.dat
solid_unpolarised_3he_pip.dat



collins.exe -DATA N

will generate and store pseudodata assigning experimental error to the calculation with parameter set N
at each kinematical bin

it also stores values of Transversity is in

transversity_u_10.dat
transversity_d_10.dat

The format

x x*h_u(x)

x x*h_d(x)

and tensor charges



// REDUNDANT NO USE
collins.exe -NO 10

will use parameter set 10 and calculate chi^2 and store information on transversity U and D and the values for tensor charge at 10 GeV^2

The values of chi2 are in a file

chi2_10.dat

The format is 

set_number set_used   chi2_pim  number_pim_bins  chi2_pip   number_pip_bins   chi2_pim + chi2_pip   number_pim_bins + number_pip_bins 


Transversity is in

transversity_u_10.dat
transversity_d_10.dat

The format

x x*h_u(x)

x x*h_d(x)